# Git Commit Guidelines

## Commit Message Format

Follow the same pattern like [Conventional Commits](mdc:https:/www.conventionalcommits.org)

```
<emoji> <type>(<scope>): <description>

[optional body]

[optional footer(s)]
```

## Commit Types

| type | emoji | description | value |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| chore | 🧹 | Build process or auxiliary tool changes | chore |
| ci | 👷 | CI related changes | ci |
| docs | 📝 | Documentation only changes | docs |
| feat | 💡 | A new feature | feat |
| fix | 🪲 | A bug fix | fix |
| hotfix | 🚨 | Emergency fix | hotfix |
| perf | ⚡ | A code change that improves performance | perf |
| refactor | 🧬 | A code change that neither fixes a bug or adds a feature | refactor |
| release | 🎉 | Create a release commit | release |
| style | 🚧 | Markup, white-space, formatting, missing semi-colons... | style |
| test | 🧪 | Adding missing tests | test |
